      "text_span_id": "intro_1",
      "text": "Hemi-sectioned spinal cord injury (hSCI) can lead to spastic paralysis on the injured side, as well as flaccid paralysis on the contralateral side",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "experimental",
      "eco_type": "animal_model",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC5555969:introduction:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC5555969",
      "text_span_id": "intro_2",
      "text": "Stem-cell therapy may offer an effective treatment option for individuals with hSCI",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "experimental",
      "eco_type": "animal_model",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC5555969:results:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC5555969",
      "text_span_id": "results_1",
      "text": "Following BMSC transplantation, motoneurons extent of shrinkage were reduced and the animals' Basso, Beattie, and Bresnahan (BBB) locomotion scale scores were significantly higher at 21 and 28 days after injury",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "experimental",
      "eco_type": "animal_model",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC5555969:results:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC5555969",
      "text_span_id": "results_2",
      "text": "the hSCI-induced elevations in scar formation, IL-1\u03b2, and cell apoptosis were reduced by BMSC transplantation",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "experimental",
      "eco_type": "animal_model",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC5555969:results:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC5555969",
      "text_span_id": "results_3",
      "text": "Corresponding elevations in the expression of STAT3 and CNTF mRNA were observed in the hSCI + BMSCs group",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "experimental",
      "eco_type": "animal_model",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC5555969:conclusion:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC5555969",
      "text_span_id": "conclusion_1",
      "text": "grafted BMSCs can significantly improve locomotor function in tree shrews subjected to hSCI and that this improvement is associated with the upregulation of CNTF and STAT3 signaling",
      "confidence": 0.95,
